"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-paris-2024-summer-olympics-river-seine-heat-rats-b2586221.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Concern and controversy has weighed heavily on the build-up to the Paris Olympics as city officials rush to present the capital in its best light and organisers work under the shadow of a corruption investigation  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  It is forecast to rain inParison Friday, and for organisers of the Olympic Games, that could be a problem.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not because the rain might put out the Olympic flame during the opening ceremony (this actually happened during a storm in Montreal in 1976, and the flame had to be reignited with a cigarette lighter), but because stormwater washes wastewater into the River Seine.\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.055126580714724e-17, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}, {\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Levels ofE colibacteria in the Seine are being monitored by stressed organisers and frazzled scientists on a constant basis, and over the past few weeks those readings have been on a hygiene knife-edge.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 1135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.115357665049746e-17, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The river is meant to host open water swimming and triathlon events next week, but heavy downpours could tip readings back towards unsafe territory, as they have been for most of the year.\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is no wonder the Paris mayor,Anne Hidalgo, put off last week'sswimming stuntfor as long as she possibly could.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1357, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is confidence among organisers that the dry mid-July weather has done enough to lower pollution levels and avoid the drastic option of cancelling the swimming leg and turningthe triathlon into a duathlon, but it is just one of a number of issues that have weighed on them in the build-up to these Games.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chief among them is security.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheseOlympicscome less than a decade after the deadliest terrorist incident in French history, the 2015 attacks on the Bataclan and other sites around Paris, which left deep scars and a city on edge.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1860, \"end\": 1874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0718371800400905e-60, \"text\": \"Bataclan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\"}, {\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This reporter was in a fan park by the Eiffel Tower at Euro 2016 when a popping noise sparked a terrifying stampede to escape what was presumed to be the sound of a gun.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It turned out to be firecrackers, but people assumed the worst.\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games arrive at a time of tension in France following the snap election earlier this month, which sawviolence break outon the streets after a shock win for the country's left-wing coalition blocked the far-right from taking power.\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2216, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1948_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.0541361255215584e-36, \"text\": \"The Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1948_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1948_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2257, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998971702975612, \"rank\": 9.264743673941713e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Protesters could be seen launching flares, setting e-bikes on fire and clashing with police.\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Security is at the heart of everything we do,\\\"Paris 2024CEOEtienne Thobois toldThe Independentearlier this year.\", \"from\": 2545, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a huge plan being put in place.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tens of thousands of people are going to be implemented and not one stone has been left unturned.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not about being confident, it is about being thorough, and to limit the risks that will always remain.\\\"\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are also concerns around temperatures whichare expected to soar beyond 30Cnext week, making all manner of events a serious health risk.\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Olympic Village, accommodation was built without air conditioning in order to boost the Games' environmental credentials, but organisers U-turned after a backlash from national associations, and a supply of 2,500 temporary units will now serve the 7,000 rooms on site.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That response has not satisfied everyone.\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sleep is increasingly considered critical to elite performance and some of the wealthier nations, including Britain, Australia and the USA, are bringing, buying or renting their own air-conditioning units.\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3479, \"end\": 3486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999986801630781, \"rank\": 1.3186801384074482e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3488, \"end\": 3497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.999994522862373, \"rank\": 5.477154926004482e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.086898345144313e-13, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We appreciate the concept of not having air conditioning due to the carbon footprint,\\\" Australian Olympic chief Matt Carroll said.\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3665, \"end\": 3675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9530783966620867, \"rank\": 0.03719628623693421, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 3690, \"end\": 3702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Carroll_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9257385252731692, \"rank\": 0.05365853658533906, \"text\": \"Matt Carroll\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Carroll_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Carroll_(basketball)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it is a high-performance Games.\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are not going for a picnic.\\\"\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hosting the Olympics is always a show of soft power to the world, and so Paris is attempting to present itself in a certain light while hiding some raw realities.\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3852, \"end\": 3857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those is rats: the city has undergone a mass purge using mechanical traps and chemicals, and shutting off sewer exit points, led by expert exterminators called the Smash Team.\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 4124, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a dark parallel, city officials have been accused of social cleansing after police broke up migrant camps earlier this month and homeless people were systematically removed from the capital's streets.\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since April 2023, almost 13,000 people on the margins of Paris - largely immigrants, people sleeping rough and sex workers - have been removed, according to a report by a group of human rights organisations and charities calledLe Revers de la Medaille(the other side of the medal).\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4387, \"end\": 4392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While government and city officials have been tasked with presenting the best of Paris, the organising committee's primary task of delivering the Games has been relatively straightforward, given how much of the sporting infrastructure was already in place and how little had to be built from scratch.\", \"from\": 4613, \"to\": 4913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4694, \"end\": 4699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only major new venue is the Aquatics Centre, though that comes with the bizarre catch that it will not host a single swimming race, despite promises that it would in the city's original bid.\", \"from\": 4914, \"to\": 5108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fina, swimming's global governing body, demands a venue capacity of at least 15,000 seats for major events like the Olympic Games, but Paris's shiny new \\u20ac175m (\\u00a3147m) Aquatics Centre will host only artistic swimming, diving and water polo in front of 5,000 fans, while the far bigger La Defense Arena will now put on the swimming.It has been reportedthat the reduction in capacity was decided as the venue's budget spiralled from its original \\u20ac70m, though a spokesman for the Paris 2024 organising committee denied this toThe Independent, insisting the decision was purely logistical.\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5245, \"end\": 5250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5394, \"end\": 5404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Defense\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\"}, {\"begin\": 5586, \"end\": 5596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5944998233608687e-33, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5636, \"end\": 5647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.031891769713505e-23, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is worth pointing out that a corruption probe still hangs over the organising committee, after French police raided the house of CEO Thobois and seized documents as part of synchronised raids on the Olympics' headquarters and the offices of companies awarded contracts to help deliver the Games.\", \"from\": 5696, \"to\": 5994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5794, \"end\": 5807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.542309990276747e-54, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The investigation into \\\"illegal conflict of interest, misuse of public funds and favouritism\\\" remains ongoing, and no charges have been brought against anyone involved.\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6163, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thobois toldThe Independenthe was shocked by the raids but added that \\\"it's part of the job\\\".\", \"from\": 6164, \"to\": 6257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All of which means organisers and city officials cannot wait for the Games to get into full swing, and for the stars to take the stage.\", \"from\": 6259, \"to\": 6394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be a year when mental health is in the spotlight, asSimone Biles returnsto perform under intense scrutiny following her struggles in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 6396, \"to\": 6545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6539, \"end\": 6544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999939457249193, \"rank\": 6.054236956352094e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty and Caeleb Dressel, two of the pool's alpha swimmers, will compete after having taken time away to look after their mental wellbeing.\", \"from\": 6546, \"to\": 6690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6546, \"end\": 6556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 6561, \"end\": 6575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their stories can be inspirational both in glory and in defeat.\", \"from\": 6691, \"to\": 6754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are many potential headline acts, like the American sprinter Noah Lyles, the Canadian teenage swimming sensation Summer McIntosh and French judo king Teddy Riner.\", \"from\": 6756, \"to\": 6924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6805, \"end\": 6813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4803366233870595e-15, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 6823, \"end\": 6833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 6839, \"end\": 6847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999984696917522, \"rank\": 1.5303100410832202e-06, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 6875, \"end\": 6890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}, {\"begin\": 6895, \"end\": 6901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9145572607309951, \"rank\": 0.0798299136565151, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 6912, \"end\": 6923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And there are always stories that emerge from thin air - think of thehigh jumpers' shared goldin Tokyo, moments that are seen and shared around the world in an instant.\", \"from\": 6925, \"to\": 7093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7022, \"end\": 7027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999939457249193, \"rank\": 6.054236956352094e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A century after its second Games in 1924, Paris will become the second city to host the summer Olympics for a third time.\", \"from\": 7095, \"to\": 7216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7137, \"end\": 7142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be spectacular, with an opening ceremony on the river and absorbing sport played out against backdrops of the Eiffel Tower and the Palace of Versailles.\", \"from\": 7217, \"to\": 7377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Seven years after it won the bid, amid a host of problems, Paris is almost ready to put on the world's greatest show.\", \"from\": 7378, \"to\": 7495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7437, \"end\": 7442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So long as it does not rain.\", \"from\": 7496, \"to\": 7524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 7526, \"to\": 7756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7577, \"end\": 7588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.031891769713505e-23, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"